West Singhbhum or Pashchimi Singhbhum is one of the 24 districts of Jharkhand state, India. It came into existence on 16 January 1990, when the old Singhbhum district was bifurcated. Chaibasa is the state headquarters.
&nbsp;
Chaibasa is a town and a municipality in West Singhbhum

Godda is a city and a municipality in Godda district in the Indian state of Jharkhand. The district has an area of 2110 km&sup2;. The district headquarters is Godda.
